title._content: "Inellan," Walter Douglas house, Channel Drive, Montecito, California. (LOC)

description._content: Johnston, Frances Benjamin,, 1864-1952,, photographer. ["Inellan," Walter Douglas house, Channel Drive, Montecito, California. Garden façade] [1917 spring] 1 photograph : glass lantern slide, hand-colored ; 3.25 x 4 in. Notes: Site History. House Architecture: Francis Townsend Underhill, built 1902, with changes for Walter Douglas ca. 1906. Landscape: Francis Townsend Underhill, from 1902. Associated Name: Edith Bell (Mrs. Walter) Douglas. Other: Originally, Francis Townsend Underhill house, as part of Underhill's La Chiquita property, enlarged by him after sale to Douglas in 1906 and rented to Helen and Oakleigh Thorne in 1917. Today: Garden subdivided. On slide: Blue star sticker. Slide used with lecture "California Gardens" as no. 51. Title, date, and subject information provided by Sam Watters, 2011. Forms part of: Garden and historic house lecture series in the Frances Benjamin Johnston Collection (Library of Congress). Published in Gardens for a Beautiful America / Sam Watters. New York: Acanthus Press, 2012. Plate 125. Rights Info: No known restrictions on publication. Repository: Library of Congress, Prints and Photographs Division, Washington, D.C. 20540 USA, hdl.loc.gov/loc.pnp/pp.print Higher resolution image is available (Persistent URL): hdl.loc.gov/loc.pnp/ppmsca.16060 Call Number: LC-J717-X97- 61
